Not exactly as assumption.

1700 vs. 1800: The 1800 has the thickest cylinder walls of any type 4
engine, and when you combine that with larger valves, and on the '74 1800
dual carbs and simple exhaust, the '74 1800 just seems to be a more robust
combination. 

